#. <section class="sutta" id="sn5.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn5.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn5.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhunīvagga"
msgstr "1. Nuns"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn5.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Vajirāsutta"
msgstr "10. Vajirā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.135"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.296"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn5.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho vajirā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the nun Vajirā robed up in the morning and, taking her bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "sn5.10:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena "
"andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya."
msgstr ""
"She wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on her return from alms-"
"round, she went to the Blind Man’s Wood,"

msgctxt "sn5.10:1.4"
msgid "Andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"plunged deep into it, and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation."

msgctxt "sn5.10:1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā vajirāya bhikkhuniyā bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ "
"uppādetukāmo samādhimhā cāvetukāmo yena vajirā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā vajiraṃ bhikkhuniṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the nun Somā feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, wanting to make her fall away from immersion, went up to her "
"and addressed her in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:2.1"
msgid "“Kenāyaṃ pakato satto,"
msgstr "“Who created this sentient being?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:2.2"
msgid "kuvaṃ sattassa kārako;"
msgstr "Where is its maker?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:2.3"
msgid "Kuvaṃ satto samuppanno,"
msgstr "Where has the being arisen?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:2.4"
msgid "kuvaṃ satto nirujjhatī”ti."
msgstr "And where does it cease?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho vajirāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then the nun Vajirā thought:"

msgctxt "sn5.10:3.2"
msgid "“ko nu khvāyaṃ manusso vā amanusso vā gāthaṃ bhāsatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Who’s speaking this verse, a human or a non-human?”"

msgctxt "sn5.10:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho vajirāya bhikkhuniyā etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then she thought:"

msgctxt "sn5.10:3.4"
msgid ""
"“māro kho ayaṃ pāpimā mama bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo "
"samādhimhā cāvetukāmo gāthaṃ bhāsatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This is Māra the Wicked, wanting to make me feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, wanting to make me fall away from immersion!”"

msgctxt "sn5.10:3.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho vajirā bhikkhunī “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ "
"gāthāhi paccabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Vajirā, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.297"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:4.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu sattoti paccesi,"
msgstr "“Why do you believe there’s such a thing as a ‘sentient being’?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:4.2"
msgid "māra diṭṭhigataṃ nu te;"
msgstr "Māra, is this your theory?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:4.3"
msgid "Suddhasaṅkhārapuñjoyaṃ,"
msgstr "This is just a pile of conditions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:4.4"
msgid "nayidha sattupalabbhati."
msgstr "you won’t find a sentient being here."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:5.1"
msgid "Yathā hi aṅgasambhārā,"
msgstr "When the parts are assembled"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:5.2"
msgid "hoti saddo ratho iti;"
msgstr "we use the word ‘chariot’."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ khandhesu santesu,"
msgstr "So too, when the aggregates are present"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sammuti → sammati (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn5.10:5.4"
msgid "hoti sattoti sammuti."
msgstr "‘sentient being’ is the convention we use."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:6.1"
msgid "Dukkhameva hi sambhoti,"
msgstr "But it’s only suffering that comes to be,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:6.2"
msgid "dukkhaṃ tiṭṭhati veti ca;"
msgstr "lasts a while, then disappears."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:6.3"
msgid "Nāññatra dukkhā sambhoti,"
msgstr "Naught but suffering comes to be,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:6.4"
msgid "nāññaṃ dukkhā nirujjhatī”ti."
msgstr "naught but suffering ceases.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ vajirā bhikkhunī”ti dukkhī dummano "
"tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The nun Vajirā knows me!” miserable and "
"sad, vanished right there."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn5.10:7.2"
msgid "Bhikkhunīvaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn5.10:8.1"
msgid "Āḷavikā ca somā ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:8.2"
msgid "Gotamī vijayā saha;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:8.3"
msgid "Uppalavaṇṇā ca cālā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:8.4"
msgid "Upacālā sīsupacālā ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn5.10:8.5"
msgid "Selā vajirāya te dasāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn5.10:8.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunīsaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Nuns are completed."
